Jenna Etheridge, News24Mogale City logo Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; The ANC has won back control of Mogale City, with Speaker Patrick Lipudi securing his position as mayor on Wednesday night.Lipudi received 39 votes and the DA's Michael Holenstein, 36. Two votes were spoilt.Lipudi was the third mayor to be elected since August.Holenstein, the previous mayor, was ousted following a motion of no confidence earlier in June.Democratic Alliance councillors underwent lie detector testing voluntarily to determine who had voted with the ANC to depose him.DA councillor Brandon May did not go through with the test and instead sent his letter of resignation to Lipudi, the party said at the time.A scheduled council meeting to elect a new mayor was cancelled last week after the DA, EFF and IFP were a no-show.&nbsp;The Speaker was forced to close council, as there was no quorum.ANC councillors at the time also requested that Lipudi charge the councillors who had not attended. While the DA did not pitch at the council, EFF councillors stood outside the building and refused to go inside. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.